Here are the most common commands to deploy and destroy a resource with terraform:


$ terraform init
==> In order to prepare the working directory for use with Terraform, the terraform init command performs the following steps:
Backend Initialization
Child Module Installation
Plugin Installation


$ terraform plan
==> This command creates an execution plan, which lets us preview the changes that Terraform plans to make to our infrastructure. 


$ terraform apply
==> This command executes the actions proposed in a terraform plan . It is used to deploy the infrastructure


$ terraform destroy
==> This command is a convenient way to destroy all remote objects managed by a particular Terraform configuration.
